 Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Blackett","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","nickname for a person with dark or fair hair, from Middle English <i>blak</i> ‘black’ (Old English <i>blæc</i>) or ‘fair’ (Old English <i>blāc</i>) + <i>hed</i>, <i>heved</i> ‘head’. See also   Black  .","nickname from Middle English <i>blak</i> ‘black’ + <i>hod</i> ‘hood’."],"variants":[{"name":"Black","meanings":["English and Scottish: chiefly from Middle English <i>blak(e)</i> ‘black’ (Old English <i>blæc</i>, <i>blaca</i>), a nickname given from the earliest times to a swarthy or dark-haired man. However, Middle English <i>blac</i> also meant ‘pale, wan’, a reflex of Old English <i>blāc</i> ‘pale, white’ with a shortened vowel. Compare   Blatch   and   Blick  . With rare exceptions it is impossible to disambiguate these antithetical senses in Middle English surnames. The same difficulty arises with   Blake   and   Block  .","Scottish: in Gaelic-speaking areas this name was adopted as a translation of the epithet <i>dubh</i> ‘dark, black-(haired)’, or of various other names based on Gaelic <i>dubh</i> ‘black’, see   Duff  .","Americanized form (translation into English) of various European surnames directly or indirectly derived from the adjective meaning ‘black, dark’, for example German and Jewish   Schwarz   and Slavic surnames beginning with <i>Čern-</i>, <i>Chern-</i> (see   Chern   and   Cherne  ), <i>Chorn-</i>, <i>Crn-</i> or <i>Czern-</i>."]}]},{"name":"Susan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["vernacular form of   Susanna .  Among well-known bearers are the American film stars  Susan Hayward  (  1918–75 ) and  Susan Sarandon  (  b. 1946  as  Susan Tomalin )."],"variants":[{"name":"Suzan","meanings":["vernacular form of   Susanna .  Among well-known bearers are the American film stars  Susan Hayward  (  1918–75 ) and  Susan Sarandon  (  b. 1946  as  Susan Tomalin )."]},{"name":"Susanna","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Susan Blackett was born about 1275, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with John Legard."},"et":{"about 1275–":"umbes 1275–Surnud","1271–1330":"1271–1330","1295–Male":"1295–Surnud","1302–1368":"1302–1368","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1302":"1302","1368":"1368","circa 1295":"umbes 1295","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","1295":"1295","about 1275":"umbes 1275","1271":"1271","Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire East Riding, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England",",Yorkshire,England.":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1275–":"noin 1275–Kuollut","1271–1330":"1271–1330","1295–Male":"1295–Kuollut","1302–1368":"1302–1368","1275–Female":"1275–Kuollut","1302":"1302","1368":"1368","circa 1295":"noin 1295","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","1295":"1295","about 1275":"noin 1275","1271":"1271","Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire East Riding, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England",",Yorkshire,England.":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1275–":"environ 1275–Décédée","1271–1330":"1271–1330","1295–Male":"1295–Décédé","1302–1368":"1302–1368","1275–Female":"1275–Décédée","1302":"1302","1368":"1368","circa 1295":"environ 1295","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","1295":"1295","about 1275":"environ 1275","1271":"1271","Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire East Riding, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre",",Yorkshire,England.":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Susan Blackett est née environ 1275, à Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec John Legard."},"de":{"about 1275–":"um 1275–Verstorben","1271–1330":"1271–1330